Question 10: Detecting and handling missing data in Excel

Answer:

As a Data Scientist, missing values must be identified and handled properly.

Tools Used:

Go To Special

Select blanks quickly

ISBLANK

=ISBLANK(A1)


Returns TRUE if cell is empty.

COUNTBLANK

=COUNTBLANK(A1:A10)


Counts missing values.

Handling Methods:

Remove blank rows

Replace with mean/median

Fill with “Not Available”

